lants she has tried-recommending bulbs and other perennials of all sorts, annuals, and woody plants-with poetic descriptions of the plants themselves as well as specific and useful cultural advice. A Rock Garden in the South includes an encyclopedia of plants alphabetized by genus and species and divided into two parts: wood and non-woody plants.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 7aGARDENING / Flowers / General.2bisacsh1 aLacy, Allen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodwin, Nancy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLacy, Allen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999z978311071360240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822378686zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822378686423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822378686.jpg  a978-3-11-071360-2  DUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999c1964d1999  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles